			<div class="content" id="post-content-2173197">
									

<p>Well, this went far from what I expected it to be.</p>
<p>The original concept was based off of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jeholopterus">Jeholopterus ninchengensis</a>, a pteranosaur that was speculated to be vampiric in nature, and how it spread a prehistoric, vampire-like virus among the human population in China. The Foundation discovered it had a weakness to Garlic, blah blah blah, it was <em>boring.</em></p>
<p>Then I wrote a bit in the draft about how they were found being served at a butcher shop in Hong Kong, and thought I should expand on that. So, I did. The result? A corporation that makes dinosaurs into frozen food and snacks.</p>
<p>Special thanks to Zyn for help with this; she gave me the idea for some of the products I used in this. Anyway, dig in, Skippers!</p>

